{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/timeoutAdd(interval:function:data:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"timeoutAdd","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interval"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc","text":"GSourceFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The given ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"function"},{"text":" is called repeatedly until it returns","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[const"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove"},{"text":"], at which point the timeout is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"automatically destroyed and the function will not be called again. The first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"call to the function will be at the end of the first "},{"code":"interval","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given interval","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(it does not try to ‘catch up’ time lost in delays)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to have a timer in the ‘seconds’ range and do not care","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"about the exact time of the first call of the timer, use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function; this function allows for more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"optimizations and more efficient system power usage."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This internally creates a main loop source using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_source_new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and attaches it to the global","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] using [method"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], so the callback"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be invoked in whichever thread is running that main context. You can do","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these steps manually if you need greater control or to use a custom main"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"context.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"time. See [func"},{"code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Function","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"func","externalID":"s:4GLib10timeoutAdd8interval8function4dataS2i_s5Int32VSvSgXCSgAHtF","title":"timeoutAdd(interval:function:data:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"timeoutAdd"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interval"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeoutadd(interval:function:data:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a function to be called at regular intervals, with the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"priority, [const","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/priorityDefault","isActive":true